  "prompt": "What are traditional British dishes?",
  "response": "Traditional British cuisine includes a variety of hearty and comforting dishes that reflect the country's diverse culinary heritage. Here are some classic examples:\n\n1. **Fish and Chips**: Battered and deep-fried fish served with chunky fries, often accompanied by malt vinegar and tartar sauce.\n\n2. **Shepherd's Pie**: A savory pie made with minced lamb and vegetables, topped with a layer of creamy mashed potatoes.\n\n3. **Bangers and Mash**: Sausages served with mashed potatoes and onion gravy.\n\n4. **Full English Breakfast**: A hearty breakfast plate that typically includes eggs, bacon, sausage, beans, tomatoes, and toast.\n\n5. **Cornish Pasty**: A pastry filled with meat (usually beef), potatoes, turnips, and onions, which originated in Cornwall.\n\n6. **Toad in the Hole**: Sausages baked in Yorkshire pudding batter, often served with onion gravy and vegetables.\n\n7. **Yorkshire Pudding**: A baked batter dish made from flour, eggs, and milk, usually served as a side with roast beef and gravy.\n\n8. **Sunday Roast**: A traditional meal served on Sundays, typically featuring roasted meat (beef, chicken, lamb, or pork), potatoes, vegetables, Yorkshire pudding, and gravy.\n\n9. **Steak and Kidney Pie**: A pastry pie filled with diced steak, kidney (often beef or lamb), and gravy.\n\n10. **Ploughman\u2019s Lunch**: A cold meal typically comprising bread, cheese, pickles, and salad.\n\n11. **Sticky Toffee Pudding**: A rich dessert made from moist sponge cake covered in toffee sauce, often served with vanilla ice cream or custard.\n\n12. **Eton Mess**: A dessert made with a mixture of strawberries, meringue, and whipped cream.\n\nThese dishes represent just a sampling of traditional British food, and many regions of the UK also have their own local specialties.",
